					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Quietust wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A homebrew cart could possibly load ROM info from an SD card and store it into RAM (and subsequently write-protect that RAM), but this would be significantly more difficult than just using Flash ROMs in the first place.</div>
<br />More difficult to design, more difficult to replicate, or more difficult to use? Compare the SuperCard SD for Game Boy Advance, which has a small boot ROM, 32 MB of RAM, and an SD card slot using SPI. It then loads game code from the SD card into RAM. Such a design wouldn't be significantly more difficult than the Famicom Disk System, except possibly for FAT parsing.
<br />
<br />Here's yet another cart design proposal. Is it feasible?
<br />
<br /><strong>SD-UNRAM</strong>
<br /><ul><li>SD-size card slot, to accept any SD-size card capable of SPI </li><li>Support circuitry for SPI </li><li>8 KB of CHR RAM </li><li>256 KB of PRG RAM </li><li>8 KB of bootstrap PRG ROM </li><li>UOROM compatible mapper circuit </li></ul>
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">SD-UNRAM Registers<br /><br />76543210&nbsp; $5xx0: Mapper Control<br />||||||||<br />||||++++- Select 16 KB bank in $8000-$BFFF<br />||++----- Mirroring type<br />|+------- 0: Write-enable RAM<br />|&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1: Treat $8000-$FFFF writes as writes to the lower 4 bits of $5xx0<br />+-------- Map ROM or RAM into $C000-$FFFF<br /><br />76543210&nbsp; $5xx1: SPI Control<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ||<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; |+- Chip select<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; +-- Invert clock &#40;required for some devices&#41;<br /><br />76543210&nbsp; $5xx2: SPI Data Out<br />||||||||<br />++++++++- Data shifted out.&nbsp; A write here begins an 8-bit data exchange.<br /><br />76543210&nbsp; $5xx3: SPI Data In<br />||||||||<br />++++++++- Data shifted in. Becomes valid n CPU cycles<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; after the last write to SPI Data Out.<br /></div></div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9" style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">tepples</a> on Thu Sep 01, 2005 7:29 pm, edited 1 time in total.</span>
