						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Here's yet another cart design proposal. Is it feasible?</div><br />Yeah, it sounds do-able.  It also would need 3V power for the SD card.</div><br />Zener diode perhaps? How clean is the VCC from the NES mainboard? And how hard is it to come across a CPLD that can speak 3.3V on one interface and 5.0V on the other?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Supporting a non-custom file system is the harder part.</div>
<br />FAT isn't that hard to parse, given that it was first developed in 1981. It appears that the <a href="http://mypage.direct.ca/c/ccovell/nesdev.html" class="postlink">Doctor PC Jr</a> uses FAT on its floppy disks. So if the Doctor PC Jr supports it, the SD-UNRAM BIOS can support it as well, right?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

