						<div class="postbody">I hate using zeners to drop voltage. It wastes power, makes more heat and there is a possibility that the zener will short out and burn up whatever it is your powering. Some semiconductor manufacturer did a study on zeners, and found that 99% of the time they short out, not go open.
<br />
<br />I've seen 3.3V regulators for pretty cheap these days.
<br />
<br />How much current do those SD cards need?</div>

